Sec. 121.171. (A) The state government efficiency 21
commission is created to review state government services and to 22
eliminate duplication and overlapping functions among state 23
departments. 24
(B) The commission shall do all of the following: 25
(1) Identify instances of duplication, overlap, or 26
fragmentation across state departments and agencies; 27
(2) Recommend methods to eliminate or improve services; 28
(3) Estimate the potential cost savings of implementing a 29
recommendation; 30
(4) Prepare and deliver, in accordance with section 101.68 31
of the Revised Code, an annual report to the general assembly. 32
The report shall be submitted not later than the first day of 33
March, and shall summarize the work of the commission for the 34
preceding calendar year. The report shall include the findings 35
of the commission and shall offer recommendations. A 36
recommendation shall not be offered unless it has been approved 37
by a majority of the commission members. 38
(C) The commission shall consist of the following seven 39
members: 40
(1) Three members of the house of representatives 41
appointed by the speaker of the house of representatives; 42
(2) Three members of the senate appointed by the president 43
of the senate; 44
(3) The director of budget and management or an employee 45
of the office of budget and management designated by the 46
director. 47

